00:57.000 --> 01:03.000
The first section that we are starting to study now is the concept of strategy.

01:09.000 --> 01:13.000
To do this, we will define strategic management.

01:13.000 --> 01:15.000
There are many of them, they were given by different authors.

01:15.000 --> 01:21.000
For example, Shendell and Hutton define strategic management as a process of determining interaction.

01:21.000 --> 01:28.000
Organization with its environment, expressed through the use of selected goals and achieving the desired result.

01:28.000 --> 01:33.000
By distributing resources to the organization in accordance with the effective plan of action.

01:33.000 --> 01:39.000
On the other hand, the famous economists Thomson and Strickland define strategic management as a process

01:39.000 --> 01:46.000
with which managers arrange and establish the long-term direction of the organization's development.

01:46.000 --> 01:53.000
They define its specific and unique goals, develop strategies, their achievements,

01:53.000 --> 01:58.000
using all possible internal and external circumstances,

01:58.000 --> 02:02.000
and take the chosen path, the action plan into account.

02:02.000 --> 02:08.000
Smith, Arnold, Beazle propose another definition of strategic management.

02:09.000 --> 02:16.000
This is a process of assessing the external environment, formulating organizational goals, making decisions,

02:16.000 --> 02:24.000
their implementation and control, focused on achieving goals in the present and future external environment of the organization.

02:24.000 --> 02:31.000
In principle, if we look at these three definitions, they have a lot in common.

02:31.000 --> 02:34.000
Therefore, we can combine them and give our own.

02:35.000 --> 02:41.000
Strategic management is a management activity related to setting goals and tasks of the organization,

02:41.000 --> 02:46.000
maintaining a number of relations between the organization and the external environment,

02:46.000 --> 02:53.000
the company's environment, which allows the company to achieve the goals it has set for itself,

02:53.000 --> 03:03.000
and allows it to remain receptive to the external conditions and requirements imposed by the environment.

03:03.000 --> 03:08.000
Now let's move on to the word strategy, the concept of strategy.

03:08.000 --> 03:15.000
Again, different authors formulate the definition of this concept in different ways.

03:16.000 --> 03:22.000
According to Steiner and Meier, strategy is the formulation of the mission of the organization,

03:22.000 --> 03:28.000
the mission of the company, its intentions, its goals, policies, programs and methods of achievement.

03:28.000 --> 03:34.000
According to Gluck, strategy is a unified, integrated and understandable plan,

03:34.000 --> 03:39.000
developed in such a way as to be confident in achieving the goals of the enterprise.

03:40.000 --> 03:44.000
Mintzberg and McHugh formulate the concept of strategy in a different way.

03:44.000 --> 03:50.000
It is a model, an example of behavior in the flow of future actions or decisions.

03:50.000 --> 04:00.000
Again, if we apply the unification algorithm, we will get a generalized definition of the concept of strategy.

04:00.000 --> 04:04.000
Then the strategy is a model of interaction of all resources,

04:04.000 --> 04:12.000
which allows the organization to fulfill its mission in the best possible way and achieve stable competitive advantages.

04:12.000 --> 04:19.000
When we have determined what a strategy is, we should define what the subject is.

04:19.000 --> 04:28.000
The subject is an organization under which an open, complex social and economic system is understood,

04:29.000 --> 04:35.000
which is a group of units, or sometimes they are called business units.

04:35.000 --> 04:45.000
On the other hand, the subject of the creation of a strategy can be the group of units, or business units.

04:45.000 --> 04:50.000
That is, it is a direction or a series of adjacent directions of the company's activities,

04:50.000 --> 04:59.000
which is independent and market-oriented, which can be a full-fledged competitor in its market segment,

04:59.000 --> 05:06.000
which is associated with the external environment, with suppliers, consumers, competitors.

05:06.000 --> 05:13.000
On the other hand, the subject of the strategy can be the so-called functional zones of the organization.

05:13.000 --> 05:19.000
This is a certain sphere of activity, which is represented by functional structural units.

05:19.000 --> 05:30.000
For example, a functional zone of the organization is management of staff or the financial sphere.

05:30.000 --> 05:38.000
Accordingly, these functional structural units specialize in the performance of certain functions

05:38.000 --> 05:48.000
and provide effective activity, both for the business units themselves, where they are located, and for the organization as a whole.

05:48.000 --> 05:54.000
When we have determined what the subject is, we need to look at the object.

05:54.000 --> 05:59.000
The object of the strategy can be three types of problems.

05:59.000 --> 06:07.000
The first type of problems is problems that are directly related to the most important goals of the company, general goals,

06:07.000 --> 06:14.000
which are focused on the future, as a rule, aimed at improving the efficiency of the company's activities,

06:14.000 --> 06:26.000
aimed at the implementation and development of the communication of goals, resources, which are necessary for the implementation of these goals,

06:26.000 --> 06:34.000
and the results that will be obtained as a result of using resources to achieve the goals set before the company.

06:34.000 --> 06:42.000
On the other hand, the second type of problems is problems and solutions related to some element of the organization,

06:42.000 --> 06:54.000
if this element is necessary to achieve the goals set, but at the moment it is either not presented in sufficient volume or is not present in the company at all.

06:54.000 --> 07:07.000
And finally, the third type of problems that can be an object of the strategy is problems related to uncontrolled external factors of the organization.

07:07.000 --> 07:17.000
The organization in its activity cannot influence everything, but is forced to adapt.

07:17.000 --> 07:22.000
It is unlikely that some company can influence the entry of Russia into the ITU.

07:22.000 --> 07:28.000
However, it will have to adapt to these conditions when Russia takes this step.

07:28.000 --> 07:38.000
In addition to determining the subject and the object, we must get acquainted with the principles of strategic management.

07:38.000 --> 07:40.000
There are five principles of strategic management.

07:40.000 --> 07:48.000
1. Perspectivity, 2. Priority, 3. Realizability, 4. Step-by-step or iterativeness, 5. Complexity.

07:48.000 --> 07:57.000
When we talk about perspective, we mean that strategic decisions should be designed for the long-term perspective.

07:57.000 --> 08:05.000
As a rule, the company's strategy is built for 3, 5, 7, sometimes 10, sometimes 15 years.

08:05.000 --> 08:26.000
For example, a factory built by one of the famous oligarchs for the production of juices was designed for a purchase period of 15 years.

08:26.000 --> 08:30.000
This is the most modern production in Russia.

08:30.000 --> 08:40.000
Priority. This principle tells us that the management must consistently adhere to the chosen path of development.

08:40.000 --> 08:49.000
The external environment is changing, the internal environment of the organization is changing, the personnel is changing, the corporate culture is changing.

08:49.000 --> 09:00.000
At the same time, the management must consistently adhere to the plan, knowing how to adjust it in accordance with the changing conditions.

09:00.000 --> 09:07.000
The main goal of the organization is not to become like a swan, a crayfish, a pike.

09:07.000 --> 09:18.000
All the desires of the organization should not be diversified, but on the contrary, they should be collected in a bundle.

09:18.000 --> 09:24.000
In fact, I said this word not in vain, this is a used term.

09:24.000 --> 09:32.000
The goals should be collected in a bundle and directed to the implementation of the main general plan of the company's development, the strategic plan.

09:33.000 --> 09:39.000
The next principle is feasibility. Goals should be achievable, but they should be difficult.

09:39.000 --> 09:42.000
The tasks are difficult, but feasible.

09:42.000 --> 10:00.000
This is the main principle, because if the goals are not achievable, after a while, people, namely people who are one of the most important resources of the organization, give up and the strategy will not be implemented.

10:00.000 --> 10:05.000
Finally, the penultimate principle is stage or iterativeness.

10:05.000 --> 10:14.000
We are talking about long-term strategic solutions, long-term strategic initiatives.

10:14.000 --> 10:25.000
They are carried out only with the help of certain events that are tactical and short-term.

10:25.000 --> 10:34.000
That is, the achievement of the final goal in 3, 5, 7 years is a multi-stage sequence.

10:34.000 --> 10:40.000
Thus, the achievement of the final goal is a multi-stage sequence.

10:40.000 --> 10:48.000
It must be constantly monitored, the implementation of events aimed at achieving goals must be constantly monitored.

10:49.000 --> 11:00.000
In the gap between the beginning of the path and the achievement of the strategic goal, certain reference points must be set, which must be monitored.

11:00.000 --> 11:06.000
Are we really going in this direction? Do we really achieve what we wanted?

11:06.000 --> 11:11.000
The difficulty here is that the process of strategic management is cyclical.

11:11.000 --> 11:14.000
It has no beginning, no end.

11:14.000 --> 11:23.000
Hence, the difficulties with building a control system, a monitoring system for the implementation of the strategy.

11:23.000 --> 11:28.000
We will talk about this in great detail in the following topics.

11:28.000 --> 11:32.000
And finally, the last principle is complexity.

11:32.000 --> 11:38.000
It is that we need all-round accounting and information analysis.

11:38.000 --> 11:44.000
Only this allows us to react in time to changes in the external and internal environment.

11:44.000 --> 11:48.000
We need to track all the narrow places.

11:48.000 --> 11:52.000
But there is also a reversal side of the coin.

11:52.000 --> 12:02.000
It is important for us not to get stuck in the stream of information and not to analyze it, only for the sake of analysis.

12:02.000 --> 12:07.000
There are companies in which the development of a strategy has never taken place.

12:07.000 --> 12:14.000
Due to the fact that the process of strategic diagnostics, the process of collecting and analyzing information,

12:14.000 --> 12:22.000
the statistics of its development, the development of the company, has been so long that it is simply impossible to reach the strategy.

12:22.000 --> 12:28.000
Please, complete the task presented in your workbook.

12:38.000 --> 12:43.000
The development of the strategy

12:43.000 --> 12:51.000
Now let's move on to evolution, to how the concept of strategy developed.

12:51.000 --> 12:57.000
Let's consider 10 schools of strategic management.

12:57.000 --> 13:06.000
Since the 1960s, strategic management as a scientific field has begun to develop rapidly.

13:06.000 --> 13:14.000
At first, the practice of research was developing quite slowly, there were few publications.

13:14.000 --> 13:20.000
Then there was a significant acceleration, but it was one-sided.

13:20.000 --> 13:28.000
In the 1970s, the development of strategic management was pulled to one side, in the 1980s to the other.

13:28.000 --> 13:31.000
In the 1990s, the offensive on all fronts was launched.

13:31.000 --> 13:36.000
And today it is a very dynamically developing sphere.

13:36.000 --> 13:45.000
The first, easily identifiable and determined schools gave a push to the subsequent ones.

13:45.000 --> 13:49.000
The subsequent ones were more complex, more detailed.

13:50.000 --> 13:57.000
The chart shows three schools that developed in the 1970s and 1990s.

13:57.000 --> 14:02.000
The design school, the planning school and the positioning school.

14:02.000 --> 14:12.000
If the design and planning schools have lost their popularity, then the positioning school still retains its importance today.

14:13.000 --> 14:19.000
Now let's take a closer look at each of the schools.

14:19.000 --> 14:27.000
The design school is associated with the description.

14:27.000 --> 14:33.000
Strategy is a unique, pre-planned perspective.

14:34.000 --> 14:50.000
The development of strategy is dominated by a management that assesses past activity and, based on it, rethinks the company's activity.

14:50.000 --> 14:57.000
Changes to the strategy are rare, but significant.

14:57.000 --> 15:02.000
All organizational activity is regulated.

15:02.000 --> 15:09.000
At the same time, the organization, if we can say so, is machine-like.

15:09.000 --> 15:11.000
Everything is centralized.

15:11.000 --> 15:22.000
The key points are the coordination of actions, the correspondence of the past, present and, accordingly, vision of the future.

15:22.000 --> 15:36.000
The development of competitive advantages of the company is realized by mechanistic work, such as SWOT analysis.

15:36.000 --> 15:43.000
Thus, we can formulate a motto that belongs to the design school.

15:43.000 --> 15:46.000
Measure seven times, cut once.

15:47.000 --> 15:54.000
The second school that developed in the 1980s is the planning school.

15:54.000 --> 15:59.000
The planning school considers strategy as a long-term action plan.

15:59.000 --> 16:06.000
Thanks to this plan of action, the company can and should shape its future.

16:06.000 --> 16:11.000
At the same time, the main thing is that the approach is rational.

16:11.000 --> 16:19.000
The most important thing in the creation of a strategy is the vision of the company, the main strategist.

16:19.000 --> 16:26.000
The main strategist is either the owner or the top management of the company.

16:26.000 --> 16:36.000
In order to form such a plan of action, the company must look back, look at how it developed in the past.

16:37.000 --> 16:56.000
That is, the development of plans uses information related to the results of the company's activities, which were carried out later, in the past, the statistics of which are accumulated in the company.

16:56.000 --> 17:03.000
Thus, the development of a strategy is a formal process, a specific process.

17:03.000 --> 17:14.000
For many works of representatives of the planning school, it is characteristic to use certain canonical methods of analysis.

17:14.000 --> 17:19.000
One of these is the SWOT analysis.

17:19.000 --> 17:29.000
How to conduct SWOT analysis, what it is, will be told to you in the following topics of this module.

17:30.000 --> 17:37.000
In fact, now I will only note the main feature of this method, the method of diagnostics.

17:37.000 --> 17:49.000
This is a strategic audit, that is, an analysis of the chances and threats in the company's environment and an analysis of its strong and weak sides, which follows from the name.

17:49.000 --> 17:55.000
SWOT is an abbreviation for the strength, weakness, chances, threats.

17:56.000 --> 18:08.000
The planning result, based on the company's diagnostics, its audit, audits of its activities, becomes ready for the implementation of the strategy.

18:08.000 --> 18:15.000
This is a document that describes who and what should do.

18:16.000 --> 18:29.000
This is a complete detail of the entire strategic concept, which provides for the detection of mid-term plans, bringing these plans to the level of one year,

18:29.000 --> 18:40.000
detailed quarterly, monthly action programs for each unit in the company, taking into account the appointment of responsibility centers,

18:40.000 --> 18:51.000
distribution of resources, calculation of budgets for each unit and the connection of all these elements with the company's strategy.

18:51.000 --> 18:56.000
That is, in fact, a hierarchy of plans, programs and budgets.

18:57.000 --> 19:05.000
The planning school was criticized by Henry Mintzberg in the work of the take-off and landing of strategic planning.

19:05.000 --> 19:11.000
He criticized the planning school on two levels.

19:11.000 --> 19:22.000
In the practical, he said that it is unlikely to seriously hope that the executors, who are isolated from the process of strategic management,

19:22.000 --> 19:32.000
from the adoption and development of the same plans and programs, will be interested in the implementation of such a plan.

19:33.000 --> 19:40.000
And if the company carries out some kind of decentralization of this process, then this is only a visibility,

19:40.000 --> 19:45.000
since the final decisions will still be made by the executives.

19:45.000 --> 19:53.000
On the other hand, he notes that any planning limits the flexibility of the company.

19:54.000 --> 20:03.000
That is, any event that happens in the environment, and, as a rule, the short-term influence of the environment,

20:03.000 --> 20:10.000
it can be either positive or negative or neutral, we are not given anything else.

20:10.000 --> 20:15.000
And not using the chances that the environment gives the company.

20:16.000 --> 20:23.000
And not carrying out any events that can protect the company from emerging threats,

20:23.000 --> 20:29.000
in principle, put its survival on the market at risk.

20:29.000 --> 20:35.000
When there is a tough plan and it is carried out tough,

20:35.000 --> 20:43.000
we understand that the company's mobility and quick response can be reduced.

20:44.000 --> 20:50.000
Mintzberg notes that planning is not an objective, not a technical process.

20:50.000 --> 21:00.000
Planning is a process that allows for the manoeuvring between the coalitions that exist in the company.

21:00.000 --> 21:06.000
It allows for the emergence of conflicts,

21:07.000 --> 21:15.000
which means that the effectiveness of the planning that this school promotes is reduced.

21:15.000 --> 21:21.000
And another point is criticized at the practical level of Mintzberg.

21:21.000 --> 21:30.000
This is a tough control system, control of the results according to the plans created, the so-called fact-analysis plan.

21:30.000 --> 21:35.000
We have planned something for a certain period of time, we have done something,

21:35.000 --> 21:42.000
we must determine the deviation between the planned results and the actual ones,

21:42.000 --> 21:48.000
analyze why it happened and take some adjustment measures.

21:49.000 --> 22:03.000
Since this tough control system adds additional effort and costs related to the implementation and implementation of the strategy,

22:03.000 --> 22:09.000
it suppresses the initiative and limits the desire to take risks.

22:10.000 --> 22:23.000
Unprecedented changes that may occur in the company's environment may not meet the company's desired response in this case.

22:23.000 --> 22:27.000
At the same time, this is a practical level.

22:27.000 --> 22:35.000
Mintzberg also talks about three fundamental mistakes in the planning school.

22:36.000 --> 22:41.000
This is a strategic level of criticism of Mintzberg.

22:41.000 --> 22:52.000
First, this is a representation of the nature of organizational reality as deterministic.

22:52.000 --> 22:59.000
The belief in the possibility of forecasting in a complex and non-permanent environment is not justified.

22:59.000 --> 23:02.000
We live in a world of uncertainty.

23:02.000 --> 23:07.000
In the morning, when we turn on the shower, we can face the fact that the water will not flow from there.

23:07.000 --> 23:16.000
Attempts to develop scenarios, attempts to develop alternative plans are good and beautiful in theory.

23:16.000 --> 23:20.000
In practice, there are many, many problems.

23:20.000 --> 23:29.000
And a standard version with the development of a pessimistic, optimistic, realistic scenario may simply not be enough in reality.

23:30.000 --> 23:38.000
The second mistake that Mintzberg notes is the division of the processes of strategy development and its implementation.

23:38.000 --> 23:42.000
In fact, this is a very true and important remark.

23:42.000 --> 23:51.000
Strategies and implementers are those between which a conflict arises.

23:51.000 --> 23:54.000
A conflict that reduces efficiency.

23:54.000 --> 24:02.000
And the intellectual potential of most employees in planning and strategy is cut off in this case.

24:02.000 --> 24:16.000
And finally, the third fundamental mistake that Mintzberg notes is the belief in the possibility of institutionalization of intuition and innovation through the formalization of the planning process.

24:17.000 --> 24:20.000
Planning is always analytical.

24:20.000 --> 24:25.000
And strategy development is a search for synthesis, a search for synergy.

24:25.000 --> 24:31.000
Therefore, the term strategic planning contains an internal contradiction.

24:31.000 --> 24:43.000
Planning destroys or cannot use the initiative and creative approach necessary for the development of a strategy.

24:43.000 --> 24:46.000
Now let's move on to the positional school.

24:46.000 --> 24:48.000
Let's try to consider it in the same way.

24:48.000 --> 24:52.000
The basic positions and some kind of criticism.

24:52.000 --> 24:59.000
The starting point for creating and analyzing a strategy in a positional school is the company's environment.

24:59.000 --> 25:05.000
It is the structure of the environment that determines the effectiveness of the company's strategy and its success.

25:05.000 --> 25:12.000
The most famous analytical method that the positional school promotes is the Porter model.

25:12.000 --> 25:17.000
Porter analyzes the environment through the prism of the five main forces.

25:17.000 --> 25:28.000
The strength of suppliers, the strength of buyers, the threat from the new environment, the danger from the substitutes and the nature of competitive rivalry.

25:28.000 --> 25:37.000
In more detail, the Porter model, the model of the five forces of Porter, or as it is now called the model of the nine forces of Porter-Matthews,

25:37.000 --> 25:50.000
where globalization is added, where informationization, society, and so on, will be considered in the next topics of the strategic management module.

25:51.000 --> 25:59.000
In this context, the essence of the development of a strategy is victory, is the struggle with competitors.

25:59.000 --> 26:09.000
Therefore, we can say that a certain military analogy is typical of the positional school.

26:09.000 --> 26:14.000
The positional school identifies the path to success.

26:14.000 --> 26:21.000
The path to success lies through the minimization of costs and differentiation.

26:21.000 --> 26:26.000
The creation of a strategy is considered as a process.

26:26.000 --> 26:29.000
The process is like a chess game.

26:29.000 --> 26:40.000
It consists of certain moves, certain choices, which a good player should know before entering this game.

26:41.000 --> 26:46.000
It is in the positional school that the tree of decisions is built.

26:46.000 --> 26:56.000
In fact, at the fundamental level, the strategic choice concerns the way to create a competitive advantage.

26:56.000 --> 27:04.000
In this context, the way is just the minimization of costs and differentiation.

27:04.000 --> 27:09.000
In the school of positioning, the main idea is analysis.

27:09.000 --> 27:14.000
Therefore, the motto of the school of positioning can be only facts.

