The main prerequisites of the cognitive school.

31:04.000 --> 31:14.000
The supporters of the cognitive school describe their activities based on the psychological concept.

31:14.000 --> 31:24.000
The strategic process is carried out through the cognitive abilities of a person.

31:24.000 --> 31:29.000
From here you can highlight the main positions.

31:30.000 --> 31:41.000
First, the formation of a strategy is a process that flows through the head of the leader or chief strategist.

31:41.000 --> 31:44.000
In fact, it is a process of knowledge.

31:44.000 --> 31:52.000
Thus, strategies are born as certain perspectives, certain concepts.

31:53.000 --> 32:03.000
In many books of representatives of the cognitive school there is a term frame.

32:03.000 --> 32:08.000
This is a set of certain emerging frames.

32:08.000 --> 32:15.000
These perspectives prescribe a way of obtaining information from the environment.

32:16.000 --> 32:24.000
Based on the information obtained in accordance with one of the branches of the cognitive school,

32:24.000 --> 32:31.000
which is called the objective, this information is decrypted using cognitive maps.

32:31.000 --> 32:36.000
It passes through all possible distorting filters.

32:36.000 --> 32:45.000
In fact, it is just an interpretation of the world that exists only in the form in which it is perceived.

32:45.000 --> 32:51.000
That is, the visible world can be modeled, structured and designed.

32:51.000 --> 32:53.000
Of course, this can be disputed.

32:53.000 --> 32:57.000
One of the famous physicists said that the best model of a cat is a cat itself.

32:57.000 --> 33:00.000
However, such a theory exists.

33:01.000 --> 33:07.000
The next school that we should consider is the school of education.

33:07.000 --> 33:16.000
The key point of the school of education is that it is based not so much on prescriptions, but on descriptions.

33:16.000 --> 33:25.000
Supporters of this school are not tired of asking a simple, but extremely important question.

33:26.000 --> 33:30.000
How is an organizational strategy actually formed?

33:30.000 --> 33:34.000
Not how it is formulated, but how it is formed.

33:34.000 --> 33:43.000
The main positions of the school of education are the complex and unpredictable nature of the external environment of the organization.

33:43.000 --> 33:51.000
Often, in conjunction with the need to constantly update the knowledge necessary for the development of a strategy,

33:51.000 --> 33:57.000
this need prevents the implementation of weighted control.

33:57.000 --> 34:04.000
After all, the development of a strategy must first of all take the form of a learning process.

34:04.000 --> 34:15.000
At least during the period when the formulation and implementation are carried out, and then these processes become inseparable.

34:15.000 --> 34:20.000
Perhaps the best student in the organization should be its head.

34:20.000 --> 34:23.000
He must be educated.

34:23.000 --> 34:27.000
But much more often there is a place for the training of the team.

34:27.000 --> 34:30.000
This is at least what happens in most organizations.

34:30.000 --> 34:36.000
As a rule, most organizations have many potential strategists.

34:36.000 --> 34:41.000
The training procedure has a developing nature.

34:42.000 --> 34:51.000
Through behavior that contributes to thinking, directed at the understanding of some actions that were undertaken in the organization,

34:51.000 --> 35:02.000
strategic initiatives are carried out by those who have the ability and resources for training.

35:02.000 --> 35:08.000
Thus, strategies can arise in the most unexpected places and in the most unusual way.

35:08.000 --> 35:13.000
Some initiatives develop on their own, by trial and error.

35:13.000 --> 35:25.000
Others are picked up by the leading leaders, key people in the company, and they support the development of these ideas.

35:25.000 --> 35:31.000
Successful initiatives, successfully implemented initiatives, form the experience of the company,

35:32.000 --> 35:40.000
which can grow into a behavior scheme, that is, into a self-developing strategy.

35:40.000 --> 35:49.000
As a rule, at the current stage, companies are trying to organize something similar through the implementation of design offices,

35:49.000 --> 36:00.000
by all kinds of activities to support any innovative ideas coming from employees,

36:00.000 --> 36:06.000
help them in development and submission of such innovative proposals.

36:06.000 --> 36:12.000
The role of the leadership, if we return to the position of the school of education,

36:12.000 --> 36:22.000
is not in the attempt to imagine in advance what the consciously developed strategies will be,

36:22.000 --> 36:27.000
but in order to manage the strategic training process.

36:27.000 --> 36:44.000
In this context, strategic management includes the skill of recognizing the interrelationship and thoughts between actions.

36:44.000 --> 36:47.000
Believe me, this recognition is very difficult.

36:47.000 --> 36:52.000
Control and training, stability and changes that the company faces.

36:53.000 --> 36:56.000
But now let's move on.

36:56.000 --> 36:58.000
The next school is the school of power.

36:58.000 --> 37:05.000
Power relationships not only entangle each organization, they are inside it.

37:05.000 --> 37:12.000
And in the school of power, two branches are formed.

37:12.000 --> 37:15.000
The first branch is the micro-power.

37:15.000 --> 37:20.000
It has to do with the game of political forces,

37:20.000 --> 37:25.000
illegitimate or illegitimate power, but within the organization,

37:25.000 --> 37:31.000
primarily in the processes of strategic management.

37:31.000 --> 37:35.000
And the second branch is macro-politics.

37:35.000 --> 37:43.000
It considers the use of power levers of the organization itself, including at the external level.

37:43.000 --> 37:48.000
Administrative resources, lobbying, and so on.

37:48.000 --> 37:55.000
If we consider the creation of a strategy as a process of planning, analysis, knowledge and training,

37:55.000 --> 37:58.000
we return to the schools that we have already listed,

37:58.000 --> 38:06.000
then it can be interpreted as a deal and as a compromise between conflicting individuals, groups and coalitions.

38:06.000 --> 38:10.000
It is enough to introduce a certain factor of unpredictability.

38:10.000 --> 38:14.000
Whether it is the variability of the external environment, the duality of the goals,

38:14.000 --> 38:18.000
various options for perceiving the situation, and so on.

38:18.000 --> 38:20.000
And this is already politics.

38:20.000 --> 38:23.000
And this is already the school of power.

38:23.000 --> 38:34.000
Thus, the school of power develops the prerequisites that were developed before them.

38:34.000 --> 38:38.000
The main positions that are characteristic of the school of power.

38:38.000 --> 38:42.000
Regarding the formation of a strategy.

38:42.000 --> 38:46.000
Formation is determined by the authorities, by the political forces.

38:46.000 --> 38:53.000
Be it processes that take place within the organization, or certain actions of the organization in the external environment.

38:53.000 --> 39:01.000
Thus, the strategies developed usually have a spontaneous nature and take the form of a position.

39:01.000 --> 39:04.000
But this is not a perspective.

39:04.000 --> 39:14.000
The micro-power considers the creation of a strategy as an interaction based on methods of persuasion, negotiations.

39:14.000 --> 39:18.000
Sometimes it is a simple confrontation.

39:18.000 --> 39:26.000
In fact, a political game around intersecting interests, forming coalitions.

39:26.000 --> 39:37.000
It is not for nothing that when developing a strategy at the current stage, it is necessary to identify the groups of interest and take into account their interests.

39:37.000 --> 39:38.000
The macro-power.

39:38.000 --> 39:43.000
The macro-power considers the organization as striving for its own well-being.

39:43.000 --> 39:44.000
How?

39:44.000 --> 39:52.000
By controlling the actions of other agents, objects presented on the market.

39:52.000 --> 39:57.000
Either direct influence, or coalitions, or cooperation with them.

39:57.000 --> 40:11.000
At the same time, the companies rely on both strategic maneuvering and development of collective strategies in various types of alliances that may arise.

40:11.000 --> 40:13.000
The school of culture.

40:13.000 --> 40:21.000
The school of culture focuses mainly on the role of culture in maintaining the strategic stability of the company.

40:21.000 --> 40:26.000
Very rarely in active resistance to strategic changes.

40:26.000 --> 40:35.000
Culture can be studied from the position of a third-party observer or from the inside, from the position of representatives of this culture.

40:35.000 --> 40:40.000
Hence, the division into two branches of the cognitive school.

40:40.000 --> 40:52.000
The first one is objective in relation to why people behave in a certain way and explains their actions with the uniqueness of social and economic relations.

40:52.000 --> 41:03.000
The second branch considers culture as a subjective process, which has nothing to do with some universal abstract logic.

41:04.000 --> 41:09.000
The main prerequisites of the school of culture are formulated as follows.

41:09.000 --> 41:19.000
The formation of a strategy is a process of social interaction based on common goals for the participants in the organization, beliefs, understandings, and goals.

41:19.000 --> 41:29.000
The belief of the individual is the result of the processes of communication to a certain culture, the culture of the organization, the company.

41:30.000 --> 41:35.000
As a rule, this is not expressed clearly, it is not verbal.

41:35.000 --> 41:42.000
Although, of course, formal education can strengthen the formation of the individual's belief.

41:42.000 --> 41:55.000
Therefore, the company can only partly characterize the beliefs on which their culture is based.

41:56.000 --> 42:02.000
At the same time, its sources of explanation may remain incomprehensible to them.

42:02.000 --> 42:13.000
Hence, the strategy takes shape primarily by perspective, and only secondarily by the position rooted in collective aspirations.

42:13.000 --> 42:15.000
It is not necessarily explicitly expressed.

42:15.000 --> 42:20.000
It is not necessary at all that the strategy is a plan or a talmud developed in the company.

42:20.000 --> 42:30.000
It is necessary to understand the structure of the organization and the models reflected in it, which protect the deep resources and opportunities of the organization, which form the basis of its competitive advantages.

42:30.000 --> 42:41.000
Thus, the main characteristic of the strategy is predeterminedness, even if it is not a fully conscious and unregulated strategy.

42:41.000 --> 42:50.000
Culture, and especially ideology, help not to change the strategy, but to preserve it.

42:50.000 --> 42:57.000
At best, they allow adjustments within the general strategic perspective of the organization.

42:57.000 --> 42:59.000
What is the danger of the strategy school?

42:59.000 --> 43:04.000
It is dangerous because it tries to disprove the need for change.

43:04.000 --> 43:16.000
Its representatives are in favor of permanence, which is so necessary to all of us in the psychological sense, of permanence in management, of a stable movement in the course planned.

43:16.000 --> 43:24.000
Culture is strong, strong, well-designed, there are resources, they are established, they are understandable.

43:24.000 --> 43:38.000
Emphasizing the importance of traditions, unanimity, characterizing changes as any complex processes, the culture school contributes to stagnation.

43:38.000 --> 43:45.000
It is very difficult to create a culture, but it is even more difficult to change it.

43:45.000 --> 43:52.000
At the same time, it is very easy to destroy, it is not a problem.

43:52.000 --> 43:55.000
There is another drawback of the culture school.

43:55.000 --> 44:08.000
It consists in the fact that strategic advantages are equated, in fact, a sign of co-existence is put between strategic advantages and organizational uniqueness.

44:08.000 --> 44:27.000
It is great not to be like others, but when differences become a goal, we come to the desire to become unique, and this leads to excessive self-confidence.

44:27.000 --> 44:32.000
The next school is the school of the external environment.

44:33.000 --> 44:48.000
If the rest of the schools consider the external environment as one of the factors that must be taken into account, it is very important, then the school of the external environment considers the external environment as the main participant.

44:48.000 --> 44:56.000
The authors who share such approaches tend to take away the passive role of the organization.

44:56.000 --> 45:04.000
The organization just reacts to the changes in the surrounding world.

45:04.000 --> 45:12.000
And the creation of a strategy is just a process of adaptation, a process of some kind of reflection.

45:13.000 --> 45:22.000
In principle, we can say that this approach takes the school of the external environment beyond the strategic management.

45:22.000 --> 45:25.000
Because there is a contradiction here.

45:25.000 --> 45:28.000
We no longer manage, we only adapt.

45:29.000 --> 45:43.000
However, the school of the external environment helps to balance the general idea of ​​strategy formation by including the external environment as a third force.

45:43.000 --> 45:51.000
We have a leadership, we have an organization, and the third force appears, the external environment.

45:51.000 --> 45:54.000
The external environment can be different.

45:55.000 --> 45:59.000
The school of the external environment highlights the characteristics of the external environment.

45:59.000 --> 46:07.000
The external environment can have stability, which varies from stable to dynamic.

46:07.000 --> 46:09.000
Complexity.

46:09.000 --> 46:13.000
The environment of the company varies from simple to complex.

46:13.000 --> 46:20.000
Market diversity, which varies from integrated to diversified systems.

46:20.000 --> 46:22.000
And hostility.

46:22.000 --> 46:26.000
The environment can be hostile or generous.

46:28.000 --> 46:34.000
The main messages of the school of the external environment are as follows.

46:34.000 --> 46:37.000
The external environment manifests itself as a set of forces.

46:37.000 --> 46:39.000
A set of forces of common character.

46:39.000 --> 46:44.000
And is the main element of the process of creating an organizational strategy.

46:44.000 --> 46:51.000
The company must either react adequately to these forces, or it will be forced to leave the market.

46:51.000 --> 46:57.000
Thus, the management is considered as a passive element of the strategic process.

46:57.000 --> 47:08.000
Its task is to understand, identify external forces and ensure the adaptation of the organization to their changes.

47:09.000 --> 47:13.000
Thus, organizations are gathered together in special niches.

47:13.000 --> 47:15.000
Ecological niches.

47:15.000 --> 47:19.000
Where they remain until their resources are depleted.

47:19.000 --> 47:24.000
Or until the hostility of the environment becomes excessive.

47:24.000 --> 47:27.000
Then the organization stops its activity.

47:28.000 --> 47:30.000
The next school.

47:30.000 --> 47:32.000
The school of configuration.

47:32.000 --> 47:39.000
The school of configuration is fundamentally different from all other areas of strategic management.

47:39.000 --> 47:43.000
The fact is that it is ready for the general application.

47:43.000 --> 47:49.000
I propose a specific way to combine all strategic ideas, all schools.

47:49.000 --> 47:53.000
Configuration and transformation.

47:53.000 --> 47:57.000
These words reflect two main aspects of the school of configuration.

47:57.000 --> 48:06.000
Stable structures of the company and the external environment are considered as configurations.

48:06.000 --> 48:10.000
And the process of developing a strategy is a transformation.

48:12.000 --> 48:21.000
If we combine all the prerequisites, then the school of configuration differs from all the others.

48:22.000 --> 48:34.000
Most of the time the company can be described as a stable configuration of its components.

48:34.000 --> 48:41.000
It is meant that for a certain period of time the company adopts a clearly defined form.

48:41.000 --> 48:44.000
Designed organizational structure.

48:44.000 --> 48:50.000
This form is adequate to a certain context.

48:50.000 --> 48:58.000
This, in turn, defines the behavior of the company and, as a result, the set of strategies that it implements.

48:58.000 --> 49:02.000
Such periods of stability are interrupted from time to time.

49:02.000 --> 49:06.000
They are interrupted by jumping to another configuration.

49:06.000 --> 49:08.000
That is, they are interrupted by transformation.

49:08.000 --> 49:17.000
The alternation of processes of stable state and transitional transformation process is built up over time in a certain sequence.

49:17.000 --> 49:22.000
This is the concept of life cycles of the organization, which we have discussed in different modules.

49:22.000 --> 49:31.000
Thus, the main goal of strategic management is to maintain the stability of the organization over relatively long periods of time.

49:31.000 --> 49:37.000
Or, at least, those changes that fit into the strategy of the organization.

49:38.000 --> 49:58.000
At the same time, during the period of need for changes, transformation, strategic management is designed to ensure the management of the process of transition from the state as it is to the state as it should be and preservation of the company's life cycle during this period.

49:59.000 --> 50:05.000
Accordingly, the process of building a strategy is reduced to the development of concepts or formal planning,

50:05.000 --> 50:16.000
to systematic analysis of the vision of the management and constant training or competitive policy,

50:16.000 --> 50:27.000
to the concentration on individual training, to collective socialization or to the limited reaction to the impact of the external environment.

50:27.000 --> 50:36.000
However, the mandatory condition is the timeliness of the actions taken, their adequacy to what is happening.

50:36.000 --> 50:46.000
The resulting strategy is taken in the form of plans, schemes, positions, prospects, tricks that are used by the organization.

50:46.000 --> 50:59.000
The conspectus presented to you contains a table in which the criteria for comparative analysis of the ten strategic management schools are given.

50:59.000 --> 51:19.000
There are three aspects. The main characteristics, including the sources, basic discipline, supporters, the implied idea, the real idea, the motto that is stated by the school and the key words that are used in the works of the representatives of the corresponding school.

51:19.000 --> 51:34.000
The second aspect of comparison is the characteristics of the process maintenance. Strategy, basic process, changes, the main acting person, organization, management of the external environment, the attitude of the school according to these criteria.

51:34.000 --> 51:47.000
And finally, the context characteristic, the situation that best corresponds to the environment, the form of the organization and the stage of the organization's development.

51:47.000 --> 52:12.000
The chart shows the ratio, the position of the different schools. Pay attention, the view of the school of positioning is turned back on the established historical data, which is analyzed and introduced into the process of creating a strategy.

52:12.000 --> 52:31.000
The school of planning, design and entrepreneurship is directed forward, but only in the future. This is the composition of the plans of the strategies. The school of design looks far ahead, to the strategic perspective.

52:31.000 --> 52:49.000
And the school of entrepreneurship looks over the edge and the other side of the nearest obstacles, creating a unique picture of the future. The school of education and power, entangled in trifles, are stuck somewhere at the bottom. They are interested not so much in the forest as in the trees.

52:49.000 --> 53:07.000
The school of education, looking at the ground, at the base, often looks down. The school of power is involved in what is happening even lower, under the stones, sometimes even underground, reaching places that organizations do not always want to advertise.

53:07.000 --> 53:29.000
The school of culture looks at everything that is happening from above. And even higher is the school of the external environment. It, so to speak, observes. In contrast to the cognitive school, which tries to look inside the process through a microscope, unlike, say, the inverted telescope of the school of environment.

53:29.000 --> 53:41.000
The school of configuration looks at the process, or, one might say, looks at this process. And now, complete the task presented in the workbook.

53:41.000 --> 54:01.000
The next section is the cycle of strategic management.

54:01.000 --> 54:19.000
According to Okofa, wisdom is the ability to see the distant consequences of current actions. The willingness to make quick gains for the sake of future benefits. The construction of a strategy implies the obligatory presence of a strategic plan.

54:19.000 --> 54:41.000
Strategic management is the sequence of actions and decisions taken by the higher authorities to develop specific strategies that will ensure the achievement of the goals of the organization. The lack of a clearly formulated strategy deprives managers of the ability to assess the goals and direction of the company's development, to manage the staff purposefully and effectively.

54:41.000 --> 55:01.000
Very often, a formulated strategy may not exist. As a rule, there is an unformalized strategy. It should be said that in this model, the strategic management model, the management process can be considered as a cycle.

55:01.000 --> 55:23.000
First, we formulate the strategic vision and mission of the company. Based on the vision, which we will talk about a little later, the goal is set. The strategy is developed. The developed strategy goes through the implementation stage.

55:23.000 --> 55:45.000
Then the assessment of the activity is carried out at each stage of the strategic plan. Changes are tracked and adjustments are made. Since the process is cyclical, revision is possible at each stage. Adjustment is possible at each stage.

55:45.000 --> 55:59.000
The cyclical process means that we do not know where we start. Indeed, from the vision, or from the setting of goals, or from the development of strategies, or from tracking results.

56:15.000 --> 56:44.000
The direction of strategic management can be as follows. First of all, it is the distribution of resources. This direction involves the distribution of limited strategic resources in the organization. Any resources used by the organization in its activities are limited.

56:45.000 --> 57:10.000
If we had a magic wand and our resources were not limited, then there would be no management and economy. At the level of strategic planning, we are talking about resources that have a long-term impact on the company's activities. Resources that can be used in many ways.

57:10.000 --> 57:25.000
Hence, the task is to form and accumulate these resources. And the formation and accumulation of resources requires time and effort.

57:25.000 --> 57:45.000
As a rule, such resources include capital in the form of money, production buildings, facilities, equipment, management talents, qualified personnel, especially today, in the conditions of a shortage of qualified personnel, technological and technical experience of the company.

57:45.000 --> 58:12.000
The next direction is adaptation to the environment. Adaptation should be interpreted in the broadest sense of the word. It covers all the actions of strategic nature that improve the company's relationship with its environment.

58:12.000 --> 58:32.000
Adaptation involves both the development of favorable opportunities and the risks and adverse changes that pose a risk to the company. Adaptation involves the study and analysis of the external environment at the moment and, accordingly, forecasting possible variants of event development.

58:32.000 --> 58:55.000
The next direction is internal coordination. It includes coordination of strategic activity for the best use of the organization's advantages and alleviation of negative consequences, as any company, any object has its weak points.

58:55.000 --> 59:11.000
As I said, any company has both strong and weak sides that it should use. The company should try to develop these sides.

59:11.000 --> 59:25.000
The next direction is organizational strategic planning. It involves the formation of organizational prerequisites, the setting and achievement of promising goals in the company.

59:25.000 --> 59:46.000
This activity involves systematic development of managers' thinking by forming a company that is able to learn from past strategic decisions. These decisions can be used in their activities.

59:46.000 --> 01:00:11.000
Another model of strategic management involves the consideration of the logical hierarchy of the stages of strategy formation. It is shown on the slide. This hierarchy shows the sequence of stages of strategy formation, from the formulation of goals to the detailed sequence of actions that are necessary to achieve this goal.

01:00:12.000 --> 01:00:26.000
If we look at this hierarchy, the choice of the mission is the most important step. In the middle of the pyramid is the formulation of long-term, medium-term, short-term goals.

01:00:26.000 --> 01:00:46.000
Finally, the development of the supporting plans and instructions for making operational decisions. These are policies, tactics, procedures, rules and budgets, in which we take into account the necessary resources.

01:00:47.000 --> 01:01:02.000
The organization's activities are divided into two parts. The business and the management system. The management system is designed to make the business work effectively and the company successful.

01:01:02.000 --> 01:01:17.000
In addition, the actions of the company can be divided into operational and strategic. Thus, we get four areas of activity.

01:01:17.000 --> 01:01:33.000
The practice has shown that in small companies, which have just been created, the first area is the operational activity, which is directly related to the business.

01:01:33.000 --> 01:01:56.000
The second area is the operational management system. This is understandable, otherwise the company cannot survive. As the company grows, as it develops, the managers are forced to pay more and more attention not only to the further development of the business, but, if the company wants to be successful, to the improvement of the management system.

01:01:57.000 --> 01:02:12.000
It should be noted that the lagging of the development of the management system from the pace of growth of the business is a common problem for many fast-growing companies.

01:02:12.000 --> 01:02:30.000
The problem is related to both management of the staff, internal business processes and decision-making. For example, one of the companies related to the intellectual business.

01:02:30.000 --> 01:02:53.000
The company is located at the start-up, it is characterized by rapid growth, the management system lags behind. What is it expressed? It is expressed in the fact that all business processes in the company are not yet registered, not yet formalized.

01:02:54.000 --> 01:03:11.000
The result is that the decisions are starting to be late. Too many agreements, it is too difficult to find a center of responsibility, it is too difficult to find someone who is responsible for this process, for this decision.

01:03:11.000 --> 01:03:33.000
Or it is difficult to reach someone who makes all the decisions, because he is involved in the whole process. Or another example. Also a fast-growing telecommunications business. The company has been growing for several years, more than five times a year.

01:03:33.000 --> 01:03:46.000
Can you imagine what kind of business level it is? The problem is related to the fact that the management system does not have time to develop for such a fast-growing company.

01:03:46.000 --> 01:04:11.000
What is the problem? During this period, 80% of the staff has changed. During this period, the company has accumulated internal fatigue from constant changes and from the constant feat that is carried out at work.

01:04:11.000 --> 01:04:40.000
Again, business processes are not yet registered, the organization is constantly in a state of change. And despite the fact that the management of the company takes various stimulating steps to make it good for the people working in the company, the salary rises, bonuses are paid, corporate events are held.

01:04:41.000 --> 01:04:56.000
However, people still have a lot of fatigue, and still the company's specialists look aside. Maybe it's calmer there, let the business develop less, but still, I really want certainty.

01:04:56.000 --> 01:05:18.000
It turns out that the faster the company grows, the faster the business runs away from the management system. Sometimes this leads to lethal consequences for the business itself.

01:05:18.000 --> 01:05:41.000
The more important role in changing conditions, the more human factor begins to play. Operational activity is easier to understand in this case. It is almost impossible to make strategically effective changes within the current company's activities.

01:05:42.000 --> 01:05:59.000
Therefore, in most cases, managers try to limit themselves to some local, local, small changes. Spending all their free time, all their efforts on what is included in the solution of all operational tasks.

01:05:59.000 --> 01:06:20.000
The strategy goes sideways. The manager is busy solving specific things. If you look at the presented schedule, you will see that the current activities should be devoted 20% of the time to operational management.

01:06:21.000 --> 01:06:38.000
And 80% should be directed to development, strategy development, strategic decisions. As I said, in a fast-growing business, everything is usually the other way around.

01:06:38.000 --> 01:06:54.000
80% of their time is devoted to the current activities and solving current issues. And only 20% is devoted to strategic management.

01:06:54.000 --> 01:07:19.000
The next section is about the mission and vision. The slide shows a picture that characterizes the importance of the stages of strategy development. And in fact, the place of vision, the hypothesis of business development.

01:07:19.000 --> 01:07:37.000
If we imagine strategic management as a process stretched into a chain, we understand that it is a transition from the state as it is to the state as it should be.

01:07:37.000 --> 01:07:51.000
There can be a huge number of ways between these two states. It is important for us to choose the path that, according to the owners of top management companies, is optimal.

01:07:51.000 --> 01:08:09.000
To do this, we need to go through several stages. We need to understand what strategic goals the company owner pursues.

01:08:09.000 --> 01:08:30.000
They are somewhere in the background. If the owner plans to sell his business, we will not tell anyone about it, but his actions will be completely different from the mission that is related to the development and promotion of this business.

01:08:31.000 --> 01:08:47.000
When we have formulated the strategic goals of the company, we move on to the formation of a vision of the future state in which we would like the company to be.

01:08:47.000 --> 01:09:04.000
To do this, we must take into account the interests of all interested groups. According to the model of the five forces of Porter, these are consumers, suppliers, competitors, and so on.

01:09:04.000 --> 01:09:25.000
Based on the vision and analysis of the internal and external environment, we must build a strategy.

01:09:26.000 --> 01:09:49.000
If we put this into a hierarchical structure, then you can see the first stage of the strategy development. Strategic diagnostics, then we develop a mission, then we develop a strategic vision or concept.

01:09:50.000 --> 01:10:06.000
Then we set goals, and the development of the strategy itself is poured into the goals of the projects, planned results, budgets, and so on.

01:10:06.000 --> 01:10:20.000
In each step of the implementation of the strategy, we will monitor it, we will control it, and as a result, we get a built-in system of management of the company's development.

01:10:21.000 --> 01:10:41.000
The main thing that can be achieved by long-term planning of goals is to see the future, which may seem insignificant, and some management problems, as well as others, which in everyday life we may not even notice.

01:10:42.000 --> 01:10:56.000
These goals are divided into several components. What position should the company take in the economy? Here, priorities are determined in the market hierarchy. Will it be a leader in the market or will it be a leader?

01:10:56.000 --> 01:11:16.000
What will be the main directions of the business? Here, efforts are accumulated in the promising sectors of activity. What is the structure of the future government? Here, the growth of the company and the development of the staff is directed.

01:11:16.000 --> 01:11:34.000
What policy will be applied in relation to the staff? Guarantees or focus on motivation? In the process of formulating goals and directions, the manager will have to tie up new important contradictions in the ideas that inevitably arise during the detailing.

01:11:34.000 --> 01:12:01.000
This task can be solved on its own. Of course, new questions will be raised, which require additional clarification. At this stage, it is possible to use the company's resources to develop the goal, to connect these resources to the goal development, to create a working group, including top management, middle management,

01:12:01.000 --> 01:12:18.000
and to include them in the work on goals, so that these goals are measurable and understandable, and, most importantly, in their implementation into the organization.

01:12:18.000 --> 01:12:41.000
Of course, the goal that the manager formulates for himself does not require a voice. It already gives a certain advantage over some intuitive management, but the same goal, shared by the team, many times increases the likelihood that it will be achieved in the future.

01:12:41.000 --> 01:13:10.000
Long-term vision. We are talking about vision now. This is a combination of rational and emotional. In addition to the final goal, in addition to the ways to achieve these goals, which must be present in the vision, there is an answer to the most secret question about the purpose of the company, its key values,

01:13:11.000 --> 01:13:29.000
and principles. The presence of a specific image of the future allows you to change to the opposite direction of the strategic management vector, moving from planning from the past, from the achieved, to planning from the future, to planning from the final goal.

01:13:29.000 --> 01:13:52.000
In this case, strategic and tactical initiatives are not assessed by the criteria of today, but by how well they will work to achieve the desired future and will correspond to the basic values that are embedded in the company, in the corporate culture and ideology of the company.

01:13:52.000 --> 01:14:21.000
Over time, long-term vision acquires a more specific form. We said that strategic management is a permanent, cyclical process. According to the formulation of the vision, the company is constantly addressing with a certain periodicity and, accordingly, corrects it, while preserving the basic principles embedded in the vision.

01:14:22.000 --> 01:14:47.000
At the same time, in the long-term vision, as in the matryoshka, smaller matryoshkas are laid down, specific short-term and medium-term strategic initiatives, which are equipped with their own micro-vision, which must correspond with the future that is formulated in the global vision, in the long-term vision.

01:14:48.000 --> 01:15:08.000
The feedback from the future allows for mutual complementation and reinforcement of the strategic and tactical initiatives. Therefore, the vision has certain roles, certain aspects and installations that it must solve.

01:15:08.000 --> 01:15:26.000
On the one hand, vision is a time machine. It gives a bright picture, which is described by large strokes. It must contain a description of the mechanism that will ensure the movement to the future state, which we designated as desirable.

01:15:26.000 --> 01:15:38.000
At the same time, the true value of vision is not only in the predetermination of the direction of movement, but in the fact that this movement will be endowed with a certain meaning.

01:15:38.000 --> 01:15:51.000
The second role is the reflection of the uniqueness of the company, its individuality, the discovery of its specific, difficult to imitate competences.

01:15:52.000 --> 01:16:04.000
The uniqueness, like nothing else, increases the value of the company in the eyes of customers, public, competitors, and serves as a prerequisite for winning the leading positions in the market.

01:16:04.000 --> 01:16:19.000
The vision must be realistic and idealistic. The global goal should be beyond the limits of today's capabilities of the company. It is necessary to make certain efforts to achieve it.

01:16:19.000 --> 01:16:36.000
But the personnel, top management, middle management must believe in the achievability of this goal, understand that with the maximum mobilization of their resources and the energy of the team, this goal is possible and achievable.

01:16:36.000 --> 01:16:51.000
The vision should inspire people, win them to go into a new orbit, to a sharp increase in personal contribution to the achievement of the goals set.

01:16:51.000 --> 01:17:06.000
The vision should be concise, clear and simple. It should be realized by every employee, regardless of his or her position in the service industry and educational level.

01:17:06.000 --> 01:17:28.000
The vision should be true to the values ​​that are accepted in the company. Economic indicators, profitability, share profitability, quality of products, if they are not tied to quality indicators, customer relations, level of personnel competence, opportunities for development, working conditions.

01:17:28.000 --> 01:17:48.000
This is a small emotional and motivational charge. Only by tying qualitative and quantitative indicators can we achieve the formation of an ideology and loyalty to the company's ideas.

01:17:48.000 --> 01:18:05.000
The emphasis should be placed on the values ​​of the company, not on abstract values. If you ask the management of Western companies, they all say that they are socially oriented, do they protect the environment?

01:18:05.000 --> 01:18:28.000
Everyone will think and say no. No, because it is economically uninteresting, not purposeful. But in fact, there are companies that have tied both the environment and economic profitability, and as a result, are positioned as socially oriented.

01:18:29.000 --> 01:18:53.000
In a way, the emphasis is placed on those values that are in conflict with the values ​​of individuals who join the organization. Each person who works in this company. For example, self-respect, professional growth, public prestige.

01:18:53.000 --> 01:19:08.000
There are people who are ready to work in a large company, even for less money, because they at least get a line in the resume that they worked in this large company. For them, this is public prestige.

01:19:08.000 --> 01:19:37.000
For example, the vision of Henry Ford's dream. I will create a car for the general public. The price will be so low that its acquisition will not become a problem for a person with a decent salary. He will be able to enjoy his family, rest in nature. Horses will disappear from the highways and cars will be perceived as the norm. This vision dates back to the beginning of the last century.

01:19:38.000 --> 01:19:58.000
Maybe the vision in the form of a motto. In the 60s, Nike formulated its vision as follows. Beat Adidas. Or Stanford University, the 1940s. Become Harvard. Well, I mean the university on the western coast.

01:19:58.000 --> 01:20:11.000
General Electric, the 1980s. The conquest and retention of each separate department of the corporation as position number one or two in their industry.

01:20:28.000 --> 01:20:44.000
This is a clearly formulated vision for the strategic needs of the company. It can be transformed for various categories of people. The company's mission only then becomes strategic when it meets three requirements.

01:20:44.000 --> 01:21:10.000
The company's mission is to provide a clear answer to a number of key questions.

01:21:11.000 --> 01:21:33.000
These questions are asked by everyone, without exception, people in contact with the company itself or its products. How does the company run its business? Its strategy, structure, employees, resources. How does the company work? What are the procedures and activities of the company? What does the company do? What are its principles and values?

01:21:33.000 --> 01:21:51.000
The mission is to develop a strategy, to make decisions, to resolve conflicts, to build a system of motivation for the staff. In addition, the mission is to form unity within the organization.

01:21:51.000 --> 01:22:14.000
The mission is to form a corporate spirit and to build a corporate culture. The mission is to form and consolidate a certain image of the organization in the representation of market subjects, be they its clients, suppliers or competitors.

01:22:15.000 --> 01:22:37.000
When we formulate a mission, we must reflect a number of aspects in its content. We must reflect the target orientation of the organization, we must reflect the sphere of its activity, products, markets, resources used, the opportunities and capabilities of the organization's competitiveness,

01:22:38.000 --> 01:22:48.000
its value system and defining traditions, the interests of society, consumers, owners and staff that we try to take into account in our activities.

01:22:49.000 --> 01:23:02.000
Thus, the mission formulation will reflect three aspects. The tasks of the company from the point of view of its main services or products, its main markets and main technologies.

01:23:02.000 --> 01:23:25.000
Simply put, we get an answer to what kind of entrepreneurship this company is engaged in, the external environment in relation to the company that defines the working principles of the company and the culture of the organization, what type of working climate exists within the company, what type of people should work in this company.

01:23:25.000 --> 01:23:44.000
Let's look at some examples of missions. A large energy company. We produce and supply energy and services in the best way, reliably and profitably, today and always, multiplying and using the accumulated potential for the benefit of society and shareholders.

01:23:44.000 --> 01:24:05.000
Another example. This mission that we have just considered is a single mission for all groups. There may be a situation when the mission is dictated by different groups.

01:24:06.000 --> 01:24:24.000
For example, in one of the groups of companies there is an external mission aimed at consumers. Professional satisfaction of the needs of a wide range of Russian and foreign clients, wholesale and retail, with high-quality goods and services at affordable prices.

01:24:24.000 --> 01:24:43.000
There may be an internal mission for shareholders. The creation of an effective mechanism of corporate and financial management of the group and the company, due to their integration into a diversified holding, to ensure the sustainable development of the business and profit.

01:24:43.000 --> 01:25:06.000
And finally, the internal mission can be aimed at employees. For example, the increase in the efficiency of the work of employees due to a more specific task setting, distribution of responsibility, implementation of motivation systems and stimulation of employees, depending on the tasks and results of the company.

01:25:07.000 --> 01:25:22.000
Please note that these three units are controversial. The managers are still arguing whether the mission should be unified or it can be different for different categories.

01:25:22.000 --> 01:25:48.000
In my experience, there was a situation when the mission should have been different. In one of the companies, shareholders at a general meeting, together with the top management, without thinking, voiced a mission for the owners and for the top management.

01:25:48.000 --> 01:26:12.000
The company was at a start-up, and therefore the mission sounded like this. Our company should grow in N-RUS for a certain period. This requires a lot of effort from both managers and staff, but there can be losses in the fight.

01:26:12.000 --> 01:26:19.000
And we can lose some staff that will not withstand this rhythm of work.

01:26:43.000 --> 01:27:10.000
Despite the fact that the company has really grown significantly over the reporting period, people left with an internal attitude that they do not need this company. If it happens that we do not withstand the rhythm, they will part with us without any problems. Naturally, this can cause negative consequences for the company.

01:27:10.000 --> 01:27:32.000
After the mission and vision are formulated, the goals are formulated. The company's goals can be associated with profitability. Then the profit that you would like to achieve is indicated, or the rate of increase in profit that you would like to achieve.

01:27:32.000 --> 01:27:44.000
Please note that the goals are usually formulated in the Smart format, which will be discussed in one of the modules.

01:27:44.000 --> 01:28:06.000
Smart means specificity, measurement, achievability, significance, and time determination.

01:28:06.000 --> 01:28:23.000
Thus, all goals can be divided into the following. Goals associated with profit, as I said. Goals associated with market proposal. Goals associated with productivity, for example, increase the productivity of labor by 10%.

01:28:23.000 --> 01:28:40.000
Goals associated with production, for example, open a new product line. Goals associated with the formation and use of financial assets, for example, attract financial assets in such a volume for such a period.

01:28:40.000 --> 01:29:04.000
Goals associated with production capacity, for example, build a new building for such a period. Goals associated with research and innovation. Goals associated with the implementation and provision of internal processes in the organization.

01:29:04.000 --> 01:29:31.000
Goals associated with regulation of the activities of such a unit in such a period. Goals associated with human resources, for example, increase the salary, reduce the turnover by 2% per year. These are the types of goals that the organization can pursue.

01:29:31.000 --> 01:29:47.000
If the goals are not formalized, incomprehensible, then there is a risk of actions that do not correspond to the goals set, do not correspond to the strategy chosen by the company.

01:29:47.000 --> 01:30:16.000
Formalization of goals stimulates discussion within the company, which reduces the risk of incomprehension or incomplete understanding of the goals set. As a result, when the assessment of their achievements is carried out in the framework of the implementation of the control for the implementation of the strategy, there will be no problems associated with the fact that people simply did not understand what goal was in front of them.

01:30:17.000 --> 01:30:39.000
If the goals are clearly defined, there may be conflicts between them. If the goals are clearly formulated and presented in the Smart format, these conflicts can be found and eliminated in the process of coordination.

01:30:39.000 --> 01:30:58.000
Moreover, if the goals are formulated, then it is possible to accurately determine the criteria for assessing both the activities of the company as a whole and each unit to which this goal is decomposed.

