the top managers of the company, who formulate the vision and goals,

01:43:18.000 --> 01:43:25.000
as well as determine the quality and quantity of the measurers of these goals,

01:43:25.000 --> 01:43:32.000
the strategic development department or the strategic development management,

01:43:32.000 --> 01:43:34.000
or the management of organizational development.

01:43:34.000 --> 01:43:39.000
In different companies, these people can be called in different ways.

01:43:39.000 --> 01:43:42.000
They are engaged in the preparation of an analytical base,

01:43:42.000 --> 01:43:47.000
on the basis of which the company's own strategy will be built.

01:43:47.000 --> 01:43:49.000
They build forecasts,

01:43:50.000 --> 01:43:59.000
they develop the working material that will become the company's strategy in the future.

01:43:59.000 --> 01:44:04.000
Very often there is a fourth participant in the development process of a strategy,

01:44:04.000 --> 01:44:06.000
these are external consultants.

01:44:06.000 --> 01:44:12.000
They are invited to demonstrate an independent view from the outside.

01:44:12.000 --> 01:44:18.000
They can expand their vision, they have experience in strategic development

01:44:18.000 --> 01:44:21.000
and they can perform the function of a moderator.

01:44:23.000 --> 01:44:32.000
It is important here that the consultant does not have a desire to write for the company,

01:44:32.000 --> 01:44:34.000
to offer it a strategy, and then say,

01:44:35.000 --> 01:44:43.000
Such a position usually ends with the fact that the strategy developed by the consultants

01:44:43.000 --> 01:44:48.000
is put on the shelf, dust is periodically blown off it,

01:44:48.000 --> 01:44:55.000
they look at the stamp, which means what a great name this consultant had.

01:44:55.000 --> 01:45:00.000
And no one is engaged in the implementation of hard-written works.

01:45:01.000 --> 01:45:09.000
If we look at the strategy and the creation of a strategy again, as a process,

01:45:09.000 --> 01:45:11.000
what will we see?

01:45:11.000 --> 01:45:16.000
First, we analyzed the external environment at the macro level,

01:45:16.000 --> 01:45:18.000
look at the graph,

01:45:18.000 --> 01:45:20.000
then at the micro level,

01:45:20.000 --> 01:45:25.000
made some conclusions and assumptions about future development,

01:45:26.000 --> 01:45:30.000
set goals and saw the impact.

01:45:30.000 --> 01:45:34.000
After all, to implement a strategy, opportunities are needed.

01:45:34.000 --> 01:45:37.000
They can be financial, resourceful, but they are needed.

01:45:39.000 --> 01:45:45.000
The competence of top management is to eliminate this impact,

01:45:46.000 --> 01:45:51.000
so that the goals acquire the status of plans, actions,

01:45:51.000 --> 01:45:56.000
which are provided by certain resource opportunities,

01:45:56.000 --> 01:46:01.000
when the centers of responsibility and control for the implementation of the strategy are determined,

01:46:01.000 --> 01:46:05.000
and clear time guidelines are established,

01:46:05.000 --> 01:46:11.000
which should be fulfilled at various stages of the company's strategic development.

01:46:12.000 --> 01:46:19.000
In his activity, during the development of a strategy,

01:46:19.000 --> 01:46:22.000
the manager can play different roles.

01:46:22.000 --> 01:46:24.000
He can be the chief architect.

01:46:24.000 --> 01:46:28.000
In some companies, one person, this can be the head of the company,

01:46:28.000 --> 01:46:31.000
takes on the role of the chief strategist,

01:46:31.000 --> 01:46:34.000
unilaterally forming the key elements of the strategy.

01:46:34.000 --> 01:46:39.000
This does not mean that he is the author of all the ideas on which the strategy is built.

01:46:39.000 --> 01:46:44.000
This does not mean that he has collected and analyzed all the necessary information.

01:46:46.000 --> 01:46:53.000
No, as a rule, the process of building a strategy is preceded by a certain brain attack,

01:46:53.000 --> 01:46:59.000
which is attracted by subordinates, professional analysis of information is done.

01:46:59.000 --> 01:47:04.000
But this means that the person, the chief strategist,

01:47:04.000 --> 01:47:08.000
acts as the chief and only architect of the strategy.

01:47:08.000 --> 01:47:12.000
He leads its development, he sets goals.

01:47:12.000 --> 01:47:16.000
In principle, the approach of the chief architect is characteristic for the company,

01:47:16.000 --> 01:47:21.000
whose heads are at the same time their owners, their founders.

01:47:23.000 --> 01:47:25.000
The next possible role is delegating.

01:47:25.000 --> 01:47:29.000
In this approach, the manager, responsible for the development of the strategy,

01:47:29.000 --> 01:47:33.000
delegates part of his powers to trusted subordinates,

01:47:34.000 --> 01:47:36.000
to the underlying managers,

01:47:36.000 --> 01:47:41.000
to competent working groups of employees of different companies,

01:47:41.000 --> 01:47:45.000
maybe to an independent working commission,

01:47:45.000 --> 01:47:51.000
maybe to a group of consultants who specialize in the development of the strategy.

01:47:52.000 --> 01:47:58.000
Delegating such events as brain attacks, analysis,

01:47:58.000 --> 01:48:02.000
development of some major events,

01:48:02.000 --> 01:48:05.000
certain components of the strategy,

01:48:05.000 --> 01:48:08.000
allows to attract managers and employees,

01:48:08.000 --> 01:48:11.000
to involve them in the process of development of the strategy.

01:48:11.000 --> 01:48:19.000
And if they participated in it, if they experienced this process,

01:48:19.000 --> 01:48:23.000
as a rule, you already support what you took part in.

01:48:23.000 --> 01:48:27.000
Accordingly, the changes that the implementation of the strategy implies

01:48:27.000 --> 01:48:33.000
will be met by developers with a positive attitude.

01:48:33.000 --> 01:48:37.000
They will support the changes that are laid down in the strategy.

01:48:38.000 --> 01:48:42.000
The next possible role of the manager is a collective approach.

01:48:42.000 --> 01:48:45.000
The manager, responsible for the creation of the strategy,

01:48:45.000 --> 01:48:48.000
relies on the help of the advice of his colleagues and subordinates.

01:48:48.000 --> 01:48:52.000
He develops a kind of a compromise version of the strategy.

01:48:52.000 --> 01:48:56.000
Linear, functional managers of different companies

01:48:56.000 --> 01:48:58.000
and different departments.

01:48:58.000 --> 01:49:02.000
There can be several very novice managers,

01:49:02.000 --> 01:49:05.000
but who have a creative approach.

01:49:05.000 --> 01:49:08.000
And, of course, veterans.

01:49:08.000 --> 01:49:11.000
Veterans who act as observers.

01:49:11.000 --> 01:49:16.000
Their task is not to be afraid to speak bitter truth,

01:49:16.000 --> 01:49:18.000
give wise advice, and so on.

01:49:19.000 --> 01:49:23.000
And finally, another role that may be inherent

01:49:23.000 --> 01:49:27.000
to a manager participating in the development of a strategy.

01:49:27.000 --> 01:49:31.000
This is the role of attracting internal reserves.

01:49:31.000 --> 01:49:35.000
In this approach, the higher management offers

01:49:35.000 --> 01:49:37.000
individual employees and a whole working group

01:49:37.000 --> 01:49:41.000
to propose proposals for the launch of new product lines,

01:49:41.000 --> 01:49:44.000
the development of new areas of activity.

01:49:44.000 --> 01:49:50.000
The main idea here is that anyone can open up in the company

01:49:50.000 --> 01:49:53.000
and thereby identify leaders and talents.

01:49:53.000 --> 01:49:56.000
Top management in this case will select proposals

01:49:56.000 --> 01:49:59.000
that are promising for them.

01:49:59.000 --> 01:50:04.000
And, accordingly, provide developers with the opportunities,

01:50:04.000 --> 01:50:08.000
both organizational and resource opportunities,

01:50:08.000 --> 01:50:14.000
so that these ideas are calculated, and then implemented.

01:50:14.000 --> 01:50:17.000
Thus, new components of the strategy appear,

01:50:17.000 --> 01:50:21.000
and their developers, accordingly, receive the opportunity

01:50:21.000 --> 01:50:25.000
to get new, unique, interesting,

01:50:25.000 --> 01:50:30.000
interesting for them, areas of activity, and lead it.

